 Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_A_Group_at_the_Florissant_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718637.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c1/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Arkansas_Riverwalk_in_Ca%C3%B1on_City_-_NARA_-_7718642.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Arkansas_Riverwalk_in_Ca%C3%B1on_City_-_NARA_-_7718642.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c1/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Arkansas_Riverwalk_in_Ca%C3%B1on_City_-_NARA_-_7718642.jpg","cap":"Arkansas Riverwalk in Cañon City","desc":"The Arkansas Riverwalk follows the Arkansas River in Cañon City. It is popular with walkers, bicyclists, birders, and other outdoor enthusiasts. Location: Location: Colorado (38.433° N 105.262° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Arkansas_Riverwalk_in_Ca%C3%B1on_City_-_NARA_-_7718642.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/45/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Aspens_on_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718638.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/45/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Aspens_on_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718638.jpg","cap":"Aspens on the Gold Belt Tour","desc":"Aspens decked in autumn's tawny hues line the Gold Belt Tour. Location: Location: Colorado (38.631° N 105.119° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Sally Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Aspens_on_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718638.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/16/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Battle_Mountain_Pullout_-_NARA_-_7718632.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/1/16/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Battle_Mountain_Pullout_-_NARA_-_7718632.jpg","cap":"Battle Mountain Pullout","desc":"Funded by a grant, the Battle Mountain Pullout is located just off the Byway. Location: Location: Colorado (38.731° N 105.162° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Sally Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Battle_Mountain_Pullout_-_NARA_-_7718632.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/36/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bicyclists_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_Byway_-_NARA_-_7718643.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bicyclists_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_Byway_-_NARA_-_7718643.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/36/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bicyclists_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_Byway_-_NARA_-_7718643.jpg","cap":"Bicyclists Along the Gold Belt Tour Byway","desc":"Many segments of the Gold Belt Tour attract bicyclists because of the outstanding scenery and low speed limits. Location: Location: Colorado (38.654° N 105.116° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bicyclists_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_Byway_-_NARA_-_7718643.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/5e/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bighorn_Sheep_along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718644.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bighorn_Sheep_along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718644.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/5/5e/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bighorn_Sheep_along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718644.jpg","cap":"Bighorn Sheep along Shelf Road","desc":"Rocky Mountain bighorn sheep are often seen along the northern end of the Shelf Road. Location: Location: Colorado (38.689° N 105.208° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Bighorn_Sheep_along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718644.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Canon_City_West_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718633.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/37/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Canon_City_West_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718633.jpg","cap":"Canon City West Kiosk","desc":"This kiosk, located in west Canon City, sits in a beautiful garden. Location: Location: Canon City, Colorado (38.436° N 105.246° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Sally Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Canon_City_West_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718633.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/f5/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Cattle_Drive_-_NARA_-_7718645.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Cattle_Drive_-_NARA_-_7718645.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/f/f5/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Cattle_Drive_-_NARA_-_7718645.jpg","cap":"Cattle Drive","desc":"Ranchers use portions of the byway to move cattle in late fall to winter at lower elevations. Ranching continues to be an important part of the rural lifestyle in this region. Location: Location: Colorado (38.418° N 105.228° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Cattle_Drive_-_NARA_-_7718645.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/09/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Florissant_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718636.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/09/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Florissant_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718636.jpg","cap":"Florissant Kiosk","desc":"This kiosk, located in Florissant, is framed by a clear blue sky. Location: Location: Florissant, Colorado (38.946° N 105.289° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Sally Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Florissant_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718636.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c1/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Four_Mile_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718631.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/c1/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Four_Mile_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718631.jpg","cap":"Four Mile Kiosk","desc":"This interpretive kiosk is located at Four Mile Park on Teller County Road 1. Location: Location: Colorado (38.946° N 105.289° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Sally Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Four_Mile_Kiosk_-_NARA_-_7718631.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/ce/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Garden_Park_Along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718652.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Garden_Park_Along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718652.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/c/ce/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Garden_Park_Along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718652.jpg","cap":"Garden Park Along Shelf Road","desc":"Garden Park, located along the southern end of the Shelf Road, was named for its farms and ranches that supplied fresh produce and meat to surrounding communities. Today, Garden Park remains largely ranchland. Location: Location: Garden Park along Shelf Road, Colorado (38.575° N 105.231° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Garden_Park_Along_Shelf_Road_-_NARA_-_7718652.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/33/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_High_Park_Road_-_NARA_-_7718653.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_High_Park_Road_-_NARA_-_7718653.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/3/33/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_High_Park_Road_-_NARA_-_7718653.jpg","cap":"High Park Road","desc":"High Park Road traverses scenic mountain parklands that have been cattle ranching country for more than 150 years. High Park Road offers impressive views of the surrounding mountain ranges and Pikes Peak. Location: Location: Pikes Peak, Colorado (38.840° N 105.044° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_High_Park_Road_-_NARA_-_7718653.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d5/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Mine_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718654.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Mine_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718654.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/d5/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Mine_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718654.jpg","cap":"Historic Mine Along the Gold Belt Tour","desc":"Over 500 underground mines were located within the Cripple Creek Mining District. These mines produced more gold than the Alaska and California gold rushes combined. Location: Location: Colorado (38.731° N 105.163° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Mine_Along_the_Gold_Belt_Tour_-_NARA_-_7718654.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/7/7e/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Smelter%2C_Florence_-_NARA_-_7718655.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Smelter%2C_Florence_-_NARA_-_7718655.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/7/7e/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Smelter%2C_Florence_-_NARA_-_7718655.jpg","cap":"Historic Smelter, Florence","desc":"Today, a lone smelter stack testifies to Florence's history as an important industrial center of the Arkansas Valley. In the early 1900s, Florence was a center for gold ore processing and oil production and refining. Location: Location: Colorado (38.401° N 105.135° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Historic_Smelter,_Florence_-_NARA_-_7718655.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/de/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718639.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/d/de/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718639.jpg","cap":"Hornbek Homestead","desc":"Hornbek Homestead, located in the Florissant Fossil Beds National Monument, is still on a clear day. Location: Location: Florissant, Colorado (38.946° N 105.289° W) Status: Public domain. Photo by Sally Pearce","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718639.jpg"},{"url":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/a/a6/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718656.jpg/1280px-Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718656.jpg","full":"https://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/a/a6/Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718656.jpg","cap":"Hornbek Homestead","desc":"The historic Hornbek Homestead, settled in 1876, was the first homestead in the Florissant Valley. It is on the National Register of Historic Places. Location: Location: Colorado (38.739° N 105.182° W) Status: Public domain. Courtesy of the Bureau of Land Management","credit":"Public domain","pageUrl":"https://commons.wikimedia.org/wiki/File:Gold_Belt_Tour_Scenic_and_Historic_Byway_-_Hornbek_Homestead_-_NARA_-_7718656.jpg"}]}